The Osun State Police command has confirmed the release of the abducted lecturer of Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile Ife, Prof Yinka Adegbehingbe. Professor Adegbehingbe, a lecturer in the Department of Orthopaedic Surgery in the university, was abducted on Sunday May 5, 2019. He was kidnapped by suspected gunmen at Apomu town along the Ife-Ibadan expressway on his way to Ife. But, his release has now been confirmed in a statement by the spokesperson of the force command in Osun state, Mrs. Folasade Odoro to NAN on Tuesday. Odoro said that the academic was released on May 6 but gave no further details on the release. 